cs.DS, cs.DB, cs.CG, cs.AI, cs.GR 

Reasoning: 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is the most likely category as the paper describes the use of a quadtree data structure and a novel recursive variant of the free-space diagram algorithm. 
- cs.DB (Databases) is also likely as the paper deals with range searching in a database of GPS trajectories. 
- cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is relevant as the Frechet distance is a measure of similarity between curves and involves geometric calculations. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is possible as the paper uses heuristics to filter potential results before computing the Frechet distance exactly. 
- cs.GR (Graphics) is less likely but still possible as the paper deals with visual data (GPS trajectories) and involves some visualization of the results.
